The first set of architectures, called No-Fused-xxitalic_x and illustrated in Fig. 3, includes a VAE (VAE-Axxitalic_x) with a latent bivariate normal distribution trained over the data coming from a single antenna of the Wi-Fi monitor  \egthe first antenna in Fig. 3  and a multi-layer perceptron (MLP) for classification.
The structure of the VAE is reported in Table I.
Our monitor contains four antennas, hence we have four architectures trained separately, one for each antenna: No-Fused-1, No-Fused-2, No-Fused-3, and No-Fused-4.
